{"cursor":"27419","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Sympathy' is a feeling and concern. Or the perception, understanding, and\nreaction to the distress or need of another human being. This empathic concern is driven by a switch in viewpoint, from a\npersonal perspective to the perspective of another group or individual who is in\nneed. Empathy and sympathy are often used interchangeably. Sympathy is a\nfeeling, but the two terms have distinct origins and meanings.\nEmpathy refers to the understanding and sharing of a specific emotional state\nwith another person. Sympathy does not require the sharing of the same emotional\nstate. Instead, sympathy is a concern for the well-being of another. Although\nsympathy may begin with empathizing with the same emotion another person is\nfeeling, sympathy can be extended to other emotional states.\n","linknr":363,"url":"Sympathy","recorded":1362535151,"links":42,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Emotions","Social psychology","Giving","Virtue"],"headings":["Causes","Evolutionary origins","Communication","Human behavior","Healthcare","Neuroscience perspectives","Child development","See also","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/US_Navy_100119-N-7948C-048_A_Haitian_woman_screams_in_pain_as_U.S._military_medical_personnel_try_to_set_her_broken_leg_at_a_clinic_at_the_Killick_Haitian_Coast_Guard_Base.jpg/220px-thumbnail.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Portret_van_een_man005.jpg/220px-Portret_van_een_man005.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c7/User-FastFission-brain.gif","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Baby_yelling.jpg/220px-Baby_yelling.jpg","//bits